properties.Name: PolicyInspectionReportCriteria
properties.Description:
The specific criteria or subjects addressed by the associated Inspection Report.

Ex:  
- applicant character
- applicant reputation
- applicant mode-of-living
- applicant finances
- applicant exposure to hazards

Policy inspection reports are normally required by Insurance companies on applicants who apply for large amounts of life insurance.    Policy inspection reports detail information to determine the insurability of the individual.    These reports are normally obtained from national investigative agencies or firms.

Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Inspection Report Criteria.

Columns.Name: CriteriaReportedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Report Criteria was reported.

Columns.Name: InspectionReportCriteriaComment
Columns.Description: Comments or additional information regarding the report criteria.
